% Retained presburger constraints (BETA spec section 2.5).
% A `presburger phi` goal defers phi as a residual constraint and is
% carried along, so several presburger checks (and later comparisons)
% are decided jointly, not one-shot in isolation. Without retention the
% first two queries would each pass their checks independently and wrongly
% report yes.
%
% Expected:
%   ?- presburger "X > 10", presburger "X < 8".  => no.  (jointly unsat)
%   ?- presburger "X = 5", X > 7.                => no.  (comparison kills it)
%   ?- presburger "X = 5", X > 3.                => yes, residual kept.
